  "prompt": "What do people think of self lender?",
  "response": "Self Lender (now known simply as Self) is a financial service that helps people build credit by offering credit-builder loans and secured credit cards. Here are some common perspectives:\n\nPros:\n1. Helps people with no credit or poor credit establish credit history\n2. Reports to all three major credit bureaus\n3. No hard credit check to apply\n4. Allows gradual savings while building credit\n5. Relatively low-risk way to improve credit score\n\nCons:\n1. Charges fees and interest\n2. Monthly payments can be seen as expensive compared to other credit-building methods\n3. Credit score improvement is not guaranteed\n4. Limited credit limit\n5. Requires consistent monthly payments\n\nOverall, many people see Self as a useful tool for those struggling to build or rebuild credit, especially if traditional credit options are unavailable. However, individuals should carefully review the terms and compare with other credit-building strategies.\n\nReviews and experiences can vary, so it's recommended to read current user reviews and consider personal financial situation before deciding.",
